## Plan Created

**File**: `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/668f9b6ea2e704c84ed4fa709b5e1f98/plan.md`
**Workflow ID**: `668f9b6ea2e704c84ed4fa709b5e1f98`

---

### Summary

Add a conditionally-rendered "Reli Suggestion" card to `DetailPanel.tsx` by matching the open `detailThingId` against the existing `nudges[]` store state. No backend changes needed — nudges already carry `thing_id`, `message`, and `primary_action_label`. The "Prepare Now" CTA calls the existing `openChatWithContext` store action.

### Metadata

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Complexity | LOW |
| Files to CREATE | 0 |
| Files to UPDATE | 1 (`DetailPanel.tsx`) |
| Total Tasks | 1 |

### Key Patterns Discovered

- Section/card pattern: `frontend/src/components/DetailPanel.tsx:219-225` — `<section className="space-y-3">` + `<div className="rounded-xl bg-surface-container-high p-4">`
- Conditional render guard: `DetailPanel.tsx:245-257` — only render when data exists
- Chat opening: `store.ts:873-879` — `openChatWithContext(thingId, title)` sets `chatPrefill` + switches `rightView`/`mobileView` to `'chat'`

### UX Transformation

- **BEFORE**: DetailPanel shows metadata and relationships only; nudges are invisible
- **AFTER**: Matching nudge renders as a secondary-accented card with a "Prepare Now" CTA that opens chat pre-filled

### Risks

- Screenshot tests will need updating (expected after UI change): run `test:screenshots:update` and visually inspect PNGs before committing

### Confidence Score

**9/10** — single file change, all data already in-flight in the store, established section pattern to mirror exactly.
